com.nimsoft.nimbus
Class NimPost

java.lang.Object
  com.nimsoft.nimbus.NimObjectSender
      com.nimsoft.nimbus.NimPost

public class NimPost
extends NimObjectSender

A Post object with PDS content

Snippet 

 .....
      // Post the object to the spooler
      // Put the PDS, to be sent, in the object using setPDS(..)
      NimPost post = new NimPost("myname");
 
      PDS pds = new PDS();
      pds.put("from","22278432");
      pds.put("tlf","22278432");
      pds.put("message","From the sender");
      pds.put("msg","From the sender");
      pds.put("id",999);
      pds.put("tekst","This is a test");
      post.setPds(pds);
      String id = post.send();
 
 ....
      // Post many messages to the spooler
      // Put the PDS, to be sent, in the object using setPDS(..)
      // Update the PDS and resend a number of times
      NimPost post = new NimPost("myname");
 
      PDS pds = new PDS();
      pds.put("int_key",0);
      post.setPds(pds);
 
      for (int i=0;i<100;i++) {
          pds.put("int_key",i);
          post.setPds(pds);
          String id = post.send();
          System.out.println("id = " + id);  // Print the confirmation id
      }
      post.close();                          // Optional (for graceful closedown of used sockets)
 
 ....
      // Post one message to the spooler
      // Put the PDS, to be sent, in the object using the constructor
      PDS pds = new PDS();
      pds.put("my_key","Some text");
      NimPost post = new NimPost("myname",pds);
      String id = post.send();
      System.out.println("id = " + id);  // Print the confirmation id
